inessinsider.com%2Fmoved-from-massachusetts-montreal-experienced-culture-shock-2024-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20moved%20to%20Europe%20thinking%20living%20and%20working%20there%20would%20be%20a%20dream%20come%20true.%20I%20wasn't%20prepared%20for%20the%20loneliness.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221429%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Illustration%20of%20a%20woman%20sitting%20alone%20at%20a%20table.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65c49c3143bb77284ba4d1c8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221072%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWhen%20Kate%20Bettes%20went%20freelance%2C%20she%20wasn't%20prepare%20for%20how%20lonely%20she'd%20be.%3Cp%3Esoleil420%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EWriter%20Kate%20Bettes%20relocated%20to%20Berlin%20but%20struggled%20with%20loneliness%20and%20productivity.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20combats%20isolation%20by%20attending%20workshops%2C%20caf%C3%A9%20work%2C%20and%20socializing%20with%20new%20connections.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBalancing%20work%20with%20an%20active%20social%20life%20has%20improved%20her%20productivity%20and%20mental%20well-being.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EEveryone%20told%20me%20working%20and%20living%20in%20Europe%20was%20a%20dream%20come%20true.%20But%20no%20one%20said%20how%20lonely%20it%20could%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20dedicated%20extrovert%2C%20I've%20always%20loved%20the%20energy%20of%20others.%20In%20Sydney%2C%20my%20hometown%2C%20I've%20worked%20in%20large%2C%20close-knit%20offices.%20Keeping%20up%20with%20my%20sprawling%20friendship%20group%20could%20sometimes%20be%20a%20welcome%20game%20of%20Jenga.%20I%20lived%20with%20my%20partner%2C%20and%20my%20family%20was%20close%20by.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20for%20a%20few%20years%20now%2C%20I'd%20been%20itching%20to%20move%20overseas%20and%20try%20my%20hand%20at%20freelance%20work.%20In%20Sydney%2C%20I'd%20worked%20in%20everything%20from%20art%20consulting%20to%20travel%20journalism%20to%20academic%20communications.%20But%20I'd%20still%20felt%20for%20a%20long%20time%20that%20an%20unknown%20environment%20would%20stretch%20my%20horizons%20and%20stimulate%20my%20writing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20following%20the%20advice%20of%20friends%20who'd%20lived%20in%20Berlin%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20spend%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20in%20that%20creative%2C%20gritty%20city.%20I%20was%20excited%20%E2%80%94%20but%20also%20apprehensive.%20And%20while%20the%20pandemic%20delayed%20these%20plans%2C%20I%20finally%20got%20my%20visa%20approved%20and%20left%20in%20April%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20was%20about%20to%20move%20to%20a%20city%20where%20I%20knew%20no%20one%20to%20work%20in%20isolation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20loneliness%20in%20a%20new%20city%20was%20impacting%20my%20productivity%20as%20a%20freelance%20journalist%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20arrived%20in%20Berlin%20with%20no%20friends%20and%20little%20idea%20where%20to%20start%20socializing.%20To%20make%20matters%20worse%2C%20I%20would%20be%20working%20remotely%20alone%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20so%20I%20would%20have%20no%20work%20friends%20to%20help%20me%20ease%20into%20the%20Berlin%20social%20scene.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGood%20friends%20do%20not%20come%20overnight%2C%20I%20told%20myself%2C%20as%20I%20pitched%20to%20new%20publications%2C%20looked%20for%20a%20place%20to%20live%2C%20and%20navigated%20the%20complex%20world%20of%20Berlin%20insurance%20and%20bureaucracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoments%20of%20loneliness%20and%20sadness%20were%20to%20be%20expected%2C%20I%20repeated%20endlessly.%20The%20mantra%20didn't%20always%20work.%20In%20the%20first%20few%20weeks%2C%20I'd%20have%20spells%20of%20pessimism%20about%20my%20new%20life%2C%20which%20impacted%20my%20mental%20well-being%20and%20usual%20enthusiasm%20to%20write.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20I%20left%20Sydney%2C%20my%20partner%20had%20made%20me%20a%20journal%20filled%20with%20messages%20and%20photos%20from%20my%20friends%20to%20get%20me%20through%20any%20moments%20of%20doubt.%20I%20looked%20at%20this%20journal%20a%20lot%20during%20my%20first%20few%20weeks%20in%20Berlin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20realized%20I%20needed%20to%20balance%20building%20my%20success%20as%20a%20freelancer%20with%20an%20active%20social%20life%20if%20I%20was%20going%20to%20be%20productive%20working%20in%20Berlin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESigning%20up%20for%20workshops%20and%20working%20in%20caf%C3%A9s%20helped%20me%20meet%20new%20people%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20like%20any%20good%20extroverted%20digital%20worker%2C%20I%20worked%20hard%20to%20connect%20with%20strangers%20and%20start%20building%20relationships%20from%20the%20ground%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20know%20you%20don't%20make%20friends%20by%20sitting%20at%20home%20all%20day.%20I%20would%20schedule%20mornings%20writing%20in%20caf%C3%A9s%20or%20at%20home%20and%20afternoons%20exploring%20my%20new%20city.%20However%2C%20this%20low-impact%20socialization%20would%20not%20be%20enough%20to%20stimulate%20my%20work%20or%20creative%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20arrived%2C%20I%20Googled%20%26quot%3Bwriting%20courses%20in%20Berlin%26quot%3B%20and%20signed%20up%20for%20the%20first%20one%20available.%20Then%20another.%20One%20night%20after%20a%20writing%20meet-up%2C%20I%20was%20incredibly%20tired%2C%20but%20one%20of%20my%20coursemates%20invited%20me%20to%20a%20spoken%20word%20session.%20I%20immediately%20agreed%2C%20even%20though%20I%20was%20exhausted.%20On%20a%20different%20night%2C%20when%20a%20friend%20of%20a%20friend%20invited%20me%20to%20a%20secret%20rave%2C%20I%20simply%20responded%2C%20%26quot%3BWhere%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJournalists%20did%20callouts%20on%20social%20media%20to%20meet%20up%20at%20caf%C3%A9s%20and%20bars%20to%20talk%20shop%20and%20make%20new%20connections.%20I'd%20respond%20and%20spend%20evenings%20swapping%20tips%20and%20industry%20jokes%20with%20other%20writers%20over%20drinks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20child%20started%20screaming%20behind%20me%20when%20I%20was%20working%20in%20a%20caf%C3%A9.%20I%20exchanged%20an%20exasperated%20look%20with%20another%20woman%20working%20there.%20We%20began%20chatting%2C%20and%20I%20discovered%20she%20was%20a%20screenwriter%20working%20on%20a%20true%20crime%20show.%20This%20interaction%20led%20to%20an%20unexpectedly%20drunken%20night%20of%20bonding%20over%20unknown%20plates%20of%20Berlin-style%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20learned%20from%20traveling%20abroad%20to%20always%20say%20yes%20to%20any%20opportunity%20to%20socialize%20in%20a%20new%20place.%20I%20still%20have%20a%20fun%20group%20chat%20with%20girls%20I%20met%20at%20the%20rave%20and%20catch%20up%20with%20the%20journalists%20and%20writers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESlowly%20but%20surely%2C%20my%20feelings%20of%20disconnection%20and%20loneliness%20rescinded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECommitting%20to%20making%20connections%20early%20on%20made%20it%20easier%20to%20feel%20settled%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20to%20approach%20my%20life%20in%20Berlin%20with%20a%20high-energy%20commitment%20to%20making%20connections%20from%20the%20beginning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20I%20pushed%20myself%20to%20socialize%20and%20make%20an%20effort%20with%20new%20people%20early%20on%2C%20I%20now%20feel%20settled%20and%20can%20focus%20better%20on%20my%20work.%20Compared%20to%20when%20I%20first%20arrived%2C%20I'm%20finding%20it%20much%20easier%20to%20write%20stories%20and%20come%20up%20with%20exciting%20pitches.%20While%20I%20still%20love%20meeting%20new%20people%2C%20I%20have%20a%20strong%20friendship%20group%20of%20funny%20people%20as%20offbeat%20as%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20first%20got%20to%20Berlin%2C%20I%20hadn't%20found%20a%20rhythm%20of%20socializing%20and%20working.%20It%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20late%20nights%20or%20spontaneous%20outings.%20Now%2C%20I%20have%20a%20healthy%20balance%20of%20interaction%20that%20suits%20me%20perfectly.%20In%20the%20evening%2C%20I%20meet%20friends%20for%20a%20sauna%20or%20clubbing.%20By%20day%2C%20I%20catch%20up%20with%20friends%20for%20quizzes%2C%20flea%20markets%2C%20or%20swimming%20in%20one%20of%20Berlin's%20many%20lakes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20combatted%20the%20loneliness%20of%20freelancing%20and%20found%20systems%20that%20work%20for%20me.%20I%20still%20switch%20between%20working%20at%20home%20and%20the%20many%20laptop-friendly%20caf%C3%A9s%20in%20Berlin%20to%20work%20and%20get%20my%20hit%20of%20low-key%20interactions%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAs%20an%20extroverted%20freelancer%2C%20I%20had%20to%20commit%20to%20making%20friends%20and%20routinely%20socializing%20outside%20work%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDon't%20accept%20feeling%20isolated.%20If%20you've%20moved%20somewhere%20new%20or%20started%20freelancing%2C%20accept%20that%20there%20will%20be%20moments%20of%20loneliness%20and%20doubt.%20Fiddle%20with%20your%20balance%20of%20working%20alone%20and%20socializing%2C%20and%20test%20and%20adjust%20it%20until%20you%20find%20yourself%20happy%20and%20fulfilled%2C%20in%20and%20outside%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20an%20introvert%2C%20it%20might%20seem%20at%20first%20like%20the%20dream%20to%20work%20by%20yourself%20and%20not%20to%20deal%20with%20other%20people.%20But%20everyone%20needs%20a%20balance%20between%20connections%20and%20alone%20time.%20You%20just%20need%20to%20figure%20out%20yours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floneliness-how-to-make-friends-remote-worker-freelancer-new-city-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707473008000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65c4ad7743bb77284ba4d399%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floneliness-how-to-make-friends-remote-worker-freelancer-new-city-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Leaving%20her%20job%20to%20freelance%20and%20moving%20to%20a%20new%20city%20simultane