%20of%20the%20core%20group%2C%20the%20Maldivian%20foreign%20ministry%20stated%20that%20India%20had%20agreed%20to%20%E2%80%9Creplace%E2%80%9D%20the%20military%20personnel%20in%20one%20of%20the%20three%20aircraft%20by%20March%2010%20and%20would%20complete%20%E2%80%9Creplacing%E2%80%9D%20the%20personnel%20in%20the%20other%20two%20by%20May%2010.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fpress-releases.htm%3Fdtl%2F37511%2FFirst_meeting_of_the_IndiaMaldives_High_Level_Core_Group%5C%22%3EThe%20Indian%20external%20affair%E2%80%99s%20readout%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20however%2C%20did%20not%20give%20the%20details%20and%20merely%20said%20that%20both%20countries%20had%20%E2%80%9Cagreed%20on%20a%20set%20of%20mutually%20workable%20solutions%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Findian-coast-guard-boats-maldives-muizzu-opposition-parliament%5C%22%3EOn%20Monday%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Maldivian%20President%20Mohamed%20Muizzu%20declared%20that%20India%20had%20agreed%20to%20%E2%80%9Cwithdraw%E2%80%9D%20its%20military%20personnel.%20That%20marked%20the%20first%20instance%20where%20the%20Maldives%20explicitly%20said%20that%20Indian%20personnel%20would%20be%20%E2%80%9Cwithdrawn%2C%E2%80%9D%20departing%20from%20the%20previous%20use%20of%20the%20ambiguous%20term%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-to-replace-military-personnel-operating-aircraft-helicopters-maldives%5C%22%3Ereplace%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20by%20the%20foreign%20ministry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThree%20days%20later%2C%20India%20finally%20acknowledged%20that%20military%20personnel%20will%20be%20withdrawn%2C%20albeit%20without%20explicitly%20using%20that%20term.%20%E2%80%9CI%20would%20like%20to%20say%20that%20the%20present%20personnel%20will%20be%20replaced%20by%20competent%20Indian%20technical%20personnel%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20MEA%20spokesperson%20Randhir%20Jaiswal%20at%20the%20weekly%20briefing%20on%20Thursday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20expertise%20for%20operating%20these%20platforms%20are%20usually%20found%20among%20ex-servicemen%20who%20had%20operated%20such%20flights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnnouncing%20the%20withdrawal%20in%20his%20inaugural%20speech%20at%20the%20opening%20of%20parliament%2C%20Muizzu%20noted%20that%20the%20withdrawal%20of%20Indian%20military%20personnel%20had%20been%20one%20of%20the%20key%20reasons%20for%20his%20successful%20electoral%20victory%20in%20the%20presidential%20elections.%20This%20demand%20had%20been%20cornerstone%20of%20the%20ruling%20alliance%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98India%20Out%E2%80%99%20campaign%2C%20which%20began%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuizzu%20officially%20requested%20India%20to%20withdraw%20its%20troops.%20Approximately%2080%20Indian%20military%20personnel%20are%20stationed%20in%20the%20Maldives%20to%20operate%20two%20helicopters%20and%20a%20Dornier%20plane%20for%20medical%20evacuation%20and%20search%20and%20rescue%20missions.%20During%20his%20meeting%20with%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20in%20Dubai%2C%20both%20leaders%20agreed%20to%20establish%20a%20committee%20of%20officials%20to%20address%20this%20request.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20core%20group%E2%80%99s%20inaugural%20meeting%20last%20month%2C%20Muizzu%20set%20a%20March%2015%20ultimatum%2C%20signalling%20the%20Maldives%E2%80%99%20desire%20for%20prompt%20action%20from%20India%20on%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707413848000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F03232814%2FMuizzu-and-Modi.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fmilitary-personnel-in-maldives-will-be-replaced-with-competent-indian-technical-personnel-india%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22On%20February%205%20(Monday)%2C%20Maldivian%20President%20Mohamed%20Muizzu%20declared%20that%20India%20had%20agreed%20to%20%26quot%3Bwithdraw%26quot%3B%20its%20military%20personnel.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fmilitary-personnel-in-maldives-will-be-replaced-with-competent-indian-technical-personnel-india%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Watch%20%7C%20Educating%20Rita%3A%20The%20Early%20Years%20of%20Brinda%20Karat's%20Political%20Career%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F08223752%2FKT-8-FEB-B-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20to%20discuss%20her%20memoir%20%3Cem%3EAn%20Education%20for%20Rita%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Brinda%20Karat%20reveals%20that%20Rita%20was%20the%20name%20she%20was%20first%20given%20when%20she%20joined%20the%20CPI(M).%20One%20of%20her%20colleagues%20called%20Chandrabhan%2C%20a%20textile%20worker%20and%20former%20wrestler%2C%20could%20never%20pronounce%20her%20name%20Brinda.%20He%20called%20her%20Birinder%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20says%3A%20%E2%80%9CMy%20repeated%20efforts%20to%20correct%20his%20pronunciation%20had%20come%20to%20nought.%20It%20was%20probably%20with%20relief%20that%20he%20enthusiastically%20welcomed%20the%20suggestion%20to%20rename%20me.%20He%20said%3A%20%E2%80%98Let%E2%80%99s%20have%20a%20name%20that%20is%20easy%20to%20pronounce.%20We%20will%20call%20you%20Rita%E2%80%99.%20From%20that%20day%20for%20the%20next%20ten%20years%2C%20I%20was%20known%20as%20Comrade%20Rita.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%2035-minute%20interview%20to%20Karan%20Thapar%20for%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Karat%20reveals%20that%20her%20first%20big%20corporate%20battle%20happened%20when%20she%20was%20working%20for%20Air%20India%20in%20London%20in%201967.%20It%20had%20to%20do%20with%20the%20right%20to%20wear%20sarees%20rather%20than%20a%20mini%20skirt.%20She%20was%2020%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20in%20London%2C%20where%20she%20immersed%20herself%20in%20the%20%E2%80%9Cnational%20liberation%20struggle%20of%20Vietnam%E2%80%9D%20and%20was%20part%20of%20the%20famous%20Grosvenor%20Square%20protests%20of%201968%2C%20that%20she%20was%20first%20drawn%20to%20Marxism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20her%20return%20to%20India%2C%20she%20joined%20the%20Communist%20Party%20Marxist%20and%20fell%20in%20love%20with%20Prakash%20Karat.%20When%20they%20decided%20to%20get%20married%2C%20they%20chose%20November%207%2C%20the%20anniversary%20of%20the%20Russian%20Revolution.%20But%2C%20actually%2C%20in%201917%2C%20the%20date%20in%20Russia%20was%2012%20days%20earlier%20(October%2025).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20reveals%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%20had%20no%20intention%20of%20being%20an%20ideal%20wife%20%E2%80%93%20communist%20or%20otherwise.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20challenges%20she%20faced%20was%20to%20navigate%20a%20career%20for%20herself%20around%20her%20husband%E2%80%99s%20position%20as%20a%20senior%20member%20of%20the%20same%20party%20and%2C%20eventually%2C%20the%20General%20Secretary%20of%20the%20CPM%20from%202005%20to%202015.%20%E2%80%9CI%20found%20that%20often%20my%20own%20identity%20as%20a%20communist%2C%20as%20a%20woman%2C%20as%20a%20whole-timer%20of%20the%20party%20for%20so%20many%20decades%2C%20was%20all%20conflated%20with%20my%20being%20Prakash%E2%80%99s%20wife.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20book%20is%20about%20the%20period%20from%201975%20to%201985%2C%20a%20decade%20during%20which%20she%20spent%20time%20in%20jail%20where%20she%20met%20Charles%20Sobhraj%2C%20who%20was%20accused%20of%20contempt%20of%20court%20and%20found%20guilty%20and%20punished.%20He%20was%20involved%20in%20several%20anti-dowry%20campaigns%20and%20worked%20diligently%20to%20help%20the%20Sikh%20community%20during%20the%20dreadful%20killings%20of%201984.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20Janata%20government%20years%2C%20when%20she%20was%20working%20with%20textile%20mill%20workers%2C%20Karat%20was%20falsely%20accused%20of%20trying%20to%20murder%20a%20police%20inspector%20whereas%20the%20truth%20was%20that%20he%20was%20guilty%20of%20beating%20her.%20She%20ended%20up%20spending%20time%20in%20jail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FgG9ZWwzzbDg%3Fsi%3D5re9gjk5IgAW89Fk%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707412230000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F08223752%2FKT-8-FEB-B-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fvideo%2Fwatch-educating-rita-the-early-years-of-brinda-karats-political-career%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20an%20interview%20to%20discuss%20her%20memoir%20'An%20Education%20for%20Rita'%2C%20Brinda%20Karat%20tells%20Karan%20Thapar%20that%20Rita%20was%20the%20name%20she%20was%20first%20given%20when%20she%20joined%20the%20CPI(M).%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fvideo%2Fwatch-educating-rita-the-early-years-of-brinda-karats-political-career%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%20Rejects%20Allegations%20of%20Election%20Interference%2C%20Points%20Finger%20at%20Ottawa%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F21173817%2F1024px-The_Prime_Minister_Shri_Narendra_Modi_with_the_Prime_Minister_of_Canada_Mr._Justin_Trudeau_at_Hyderabad_House_in_New_Delhi_on_February_23_2018_1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20After%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20public%20inquiry%20into%20foreign%20interference%20in%20elections%20formally%20began%20to%20examine%20India%E2%80%99s%20role%2C%20New%20Delhi%20rebuffed%20the%20allegations%20and%20contended%20that%20it%20was%20Ottawa%20that%20interfered%20in%20the%20internal%20affairs%20of%20the%20South%20Asian%20nation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fcanadas-probe-panel-to-examine-indias-alleged-role-in-the-last-two-federal-elections%5C%22%3EOver%20two%20weeks%20ago%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20Public%20Inquiry%20into%20Foreign%20Interference%20in%20Federal%20Electoral%20Processes%20and%20Democratic%20Institutions%20announced%20that%20it%20has%20requested%20the%20Canadian%20government%20to%20provide%20information%20%E2%80%9Crelating%20to%20alleged%20interference%20by%20India%20related%20to%20the%202019%20and%202021%20elections%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUpon%20its%20launch%20in%20September%202023%2C%20the%20Commission%20explicitly%20stated%20its%20intention%20to%20investigate%20interference%20by%20China%2C%20Russia%2C%20and%20unspecified%20%E2%80%9Cforeign%20actors%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20initial%20phase%20of%20inquiries.%20In%20the%20recent%20press%20release%2C%20expanded%20its%20investigation%20to%20include%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Thursday%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20expressed%20outrage%20over%20the%20inclusion%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20seen%20media%20reports%20about%20the%20Canadian%20Commission%20enquiring%20into%20foreign%20interference.%20We%20strongly%20reject%20such%20baseless%20allegations%20of%20Indian%20interference%20in%20Canadian%20elections.%20It%20is%20not%20Government%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20policy%20to%20interfere%20in%20democratic%20processes%20of%20other%20countries%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20MEA%20spokesperson%20Randhir%20Jaiswal%20at%20the%20weekly%20media%20briefing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20he%20countered%20by%20accusing%20Ottawa%20of%20meddling%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20domestic%20politics.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20fact%2C%20it%20is%20Canada%20which%20has%20been%20interfering%20in%20our%20internal%20affairs.%20We%20have%20been%20raising%20this%20issue%20regularly%20with%20them.%20We%20continue%20to%20call%20on%20Canada%20to%20take%20effective%20measures%20to%20address%20our%20core%20concerns%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20Canadian%20outlet%20